1
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:18,100
Coach, my heart's telling
me that I love him,

2
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:20,433
but my mind is saying otherwise.

3
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,000
It's because of what his family
did to my mom.

4
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,500
Please talk to me.

5
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,967
Don't be unfair!

6
00:00:26,033 --> 00:00:28,233
Your family's being unfair
to my mom too.

7
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:29,367
What do you mean?

8
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:30,867
Please don't follow me.

9
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:31,867
Just leave me alone.

10
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:32,967
Yen!

11
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:39,500
Hey! You bastard!

12
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:45,900
He is Rina's brother!

13
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:48,733
Rina had you robbed to take
revenge on you.

14
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,000
Ma'am, someone's looking for you
outside.

15
00:00:51,067 --> 00:00:52,033
Who is it?

16
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:53,067
She said her name was Amanda.

17
00:00:53,133 --> 00:00:54,233
We don't owe you anything!

18
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:57,533
You owe me a lot! And I know
you're using Zandro

19
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,467
to make my life miserable.

20
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:02,400
Where do you want your head
to drop?

21
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:04,300
On your right or left?

22
00:01:04,367 --> 00:01:06,700
I don't know why our family
keeps crossing paths

23
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,333
with Rina's!

24
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,800
I've crossed paths
with her son too.

25
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:12,200
What do you mean?

26
00:01:12,267 --> 00:01:14,367
The guy that was with me
on the island before.

27
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,367
He is Rina's son.

28
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:17,967
- Give me that!
- You'll hurt her!

29
00:01:18,033 --> 00:01:19,200
- Give it to me!
- No!

30
00:01:19,267 --> 00:01:20,533
- No.
- Fine!

31
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,167
You're like the ground we're
stepping and spitting on!

32
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,500
Mom! My God!

33
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:25,867
- This is what you deserve.
- Don't do that!

34
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,000
- You deserve this!
- Don't you dare!

35
00:01:27,067 --> 00:01:28,233
Oh my God!

36
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,533
Haven't you had enough?

37
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,767
You hurt my whole family
when you murdered my brother!

38
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:34,100
Get out of here before I call
the cops on you.

39
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:36,667
Rina's son is just like her!

40
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:37,933
They're both monsters!

41
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,667
- Mom!
- You left your lunch at home.

42
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,233
Thank you, Mom.

43
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,367
I will do everything
for my daughter.

44
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:48,500
You know how much I love you.

45
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,133
Next time, you don't have
to bring this here.

46
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,533
I can get lunch here.

47
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,100
What do you mean you'll get
lunch here?

48
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:01,733
You don't have money.

49
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,867
This is the least I can do
for you. Okay?

50
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:06,733
Let me do this.

51
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:11,233
Get out of here before I call
the cops on you!

52
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,267
You can't scare me!

53
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:17,267
I spent eight years in jail
because of your mom!

54
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:20,733
Did I see it right?

55
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,900
No, she can't be Yenyen's mom.

56
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:32,333
I'd been away from you.

57
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:38,600
I just want to do the things
I couldn't do for you before.

58
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:41,900
I just miss taking care of you.

59
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:44,033
That sounds like music
to my ears.

60
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:49,233
Honestly, I've been wanting to
experience this for a long time.

61
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:53,133
To have you here with me.

62
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:57,267
I will take care of you
my whole life.

63
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,733
No one can tear us apart.

64
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:04,600
I will never let us get
separated again.

65
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:10,267
So whenever I have time,
I'll come here to pick you up.

66
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:11,400
Mom! You don't have to.

67
00:03:11,467 --> 00:03:15,467
Especially after what happened
last night.

68
00:03:15,533 --> 00:03:19,367
I don't want Rina to take her
anger out on you.

69
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,200
Don't be unfair!

70
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:24,700
Yes, it's unfair.

71
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:28,033
Just how unfair your family's
been to my mom.

72
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:32,167
Now I know.

73
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:35,167
Yenyen knew about it,
but she didn't tell me.

74
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,367
Mom, don't worry about me.

75
00:03:39,433 --> 00:03:40,767
I'm okay.

76
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,167
How can I not worry about you?

77
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,900
You don't even
have a cell phone.

78
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:45,900
How can I contact you?

79
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:50,967
That's why I'm going to borrow
some money to buy you a phone.

80
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:54,367
So I can stop worrying.

81
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:56,700
Mom, I don't need a cell phone.

82
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:57,933
We don't need to get one now.

83
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,800
And we have a lot of bills
to pay.

84
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,467
I'll be fine without a phone.

85
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:08,367
- Okay.
- I can handle myself.

86
00:04:08,433 --> 00:04:10,167
Okay. Don't forget
to eat your lunch.

87
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:12,833
- Okay, Mom. I need to go.
- Okay.

88
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,600
We might end up crying
our eyes out.

89
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:17,233
It would be embarrassing.

90
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:19,300
I'm actually near tears.

91
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:23,333
- Okay, bye. Study hard.
- Bye, Mom. Take care.

92
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:36,367
Rina...

93
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:40,533
The maids told me about
what happened last night.

94
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,567
Are you going to keep
fighting with Amanda?

95
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,233
Please, Victor...

96
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:53,967
before you get mad,
know all the facts first.

97
00:04:55,500 --> 00:05:01,300
Amanda came here and started
a war in my own home!

98
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:06,367
So I just did a counterattack.

99
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:07,933
She wouldn't try to attack you

100
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,433
if you didn't do anything
to her.

101
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,933
Just leave Amanda alone.

102
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,533
Put an end to this war
that you keep on promoting.

103
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,767
You know what's worse?

104
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,900
Your son saw what you did.

105
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,667
Red just got back from a
tragedy.

106
00:05:25,733 --> 00:05:29,567
Do you think this will help him?

107
00:05:29,633 --> 00:05:32,200
How long will you stay
like that?

108
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,867
The only way I'll stop

109
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:41,467
is when I get justice
for my son's death.

110
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:45,233
And besides, I'm also doing this
for Red.

111
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,367
What about you?

112
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:50,167
You're doing this for you
to move on.

113
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:52,633
Just for yourself.

114
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,433
And for what?

115
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:00,667
To keep your good reputation
with the rural banks.

116
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:08,367
I'll only stop once
Amanda's gone.

117
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:14,067
I will do anything to put her
back in jail.

118
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:16,800
So up until then, Victor...

119
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:20,267
deal with the war.

120
00:06:36,733 --> 00:06:39,867
What do you need, Son?

121
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:41,367
If you're going
to buy rice cakes,

122
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,200
you'll have to wait
'till next time.

123
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:45,200
I dropped this on the ground.

124
00:06:45,267 --> 00:06:47,533
Next time, okay?

125
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,700
No, it's fine.

126
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,967
Amanda, why the long face?

127
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,867
You sold all your rice cakes.

128
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,100
So why do you look like
you went bankrupt?

129
00:07:34,167 --> 00:07:38,700
I don't know, but I feel scared,
Dindi.

130
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:39,800
Scared of what?

131
00:07:39,867 --> 00:07:42,300
I'm scared for Eden.

132
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:44,567
Especially when I found out

133
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:47,367
that Rina's son survived
the plane crash too.

134
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:54,033
Our world is getting smaller.

135
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:58,633
And then they go
to the same school.

136
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:02,400
What if the two of them meet?

137
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,833
What if he takes his anger
out on her?

138
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:08,733
I don't want Eden to experience
what I went through

139
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,167
because of Rina.

140
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,467
You know what, Amanda...

141
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:16,933
That campus is huge!

142
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:21,133
It's so huge that they might not
see each other.

143
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,533
I don't know.

144
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:26,867
But I'm scared for my daughter.

145
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:29,233
I want to get her away
from here.

146
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,000
But where will we go?

147
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:33,833
I don't have any money to get
away from this city.

148
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:45,367
Yenyen.

149
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:55,300
Now I know why you're
avoiding me.

150
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:03,033
Your mom is the reason
my brother died.

151
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,933
It's true, right?

152
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,333
Your mom was imprisoned because
she killed my brother.

153
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:21,133
My mom is innocent, Red.

154
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:24,800
She's not involved in your
brother's murder.

155
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:29,800
Your family did her wrong.

156
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:34,533
They put an innocent person
in jail.

157
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:38,700
My family did the right thing
for my brother!

158
00:09:38,767 --> 00:09:43,400
It's not right to blame my mom
for a crime she didn't do.

159
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:46,900
I'm defending her because
I know she's telling the truth.

160
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:49,500
You knew everything?

161
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,167
Since when?

162
00:09:54,667 --> 00:10:00,267
Why didn't you tell me my
family's connected to your mom?

163
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:03,500
What for?

164
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:05,733
Will it change anything?

165
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,800
Your family still put my mom
in jail.

166
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:12,400
Our family still hates
each other.

167
00:10:12,467 --> 00:10:15,033
That's why I'm making things
easier for you, Red.

168
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:17,833
That's why I'm staying away
from you.

169
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,967
Yen!

170
00:10:21,033 --> 00:10:23,200
We've been through a lot
together.

171
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:27,467
Do you think I don't deserve
to know the truth?

172
00:10:27,533 --> 00:10:30,600
Okay, fine.

173
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:33,900
Now that you know the truth...

174
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,167
Is there anything you can do
to change our situation?

175
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,900
Will you still love me?

176
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:45,233
I've collected almost all
the money they owe us.

177
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:48,533
But some don't want to pay up.

178
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,933
What do you want me
to do with them?

179
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:53,967
The usual.

180
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:55,533
Make them pay another way.

181
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:01,133
They'll come to their senses.

182
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,433
The same way you do to Amanda.

183
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:13,700
You know, Amanda's been
bothering me more and more.

184
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:16,667
My family's getting affected
by it.

185
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:18,300
I want to save my family.

186
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:23,100
I want to do everything
I can for my family.

187
00:11:23,167 --> 00:11:27,667
If I can kill Amanda myself,
I will.

188
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:31,500
But I don't want her criminal
blood on my hands.

189
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:33,800
Okay, so...

190
00:11:33,867 --> 00:11:36,833
What do you want me to do?

191
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:39,667
I want you to do two things
for me.

192
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,967
Number one...

193
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:47,100
You know my favorite brand
of bags, right?

194
00:11:47,167 --> 00:11:49,700
- Of course.
- Okay.

195
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:52,200
I want you to buy me the latest.

196
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:55,300
The latest handbag...

197
00:11:55,367 --> 00:11:56,967
to ease my anxiety.

198
00:11:58,700 --> 00:11:59,667
And number two...

199
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:07,300
I want that woman back in jail.

200
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:13,167
And I have a plan.

201
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:26,333
You can't answer that, right?

202
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,933
Because you know it's true.

203
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:37,067
Let's just accept the fact that
we're not meant for each other.

204
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:39,833
Because I've already
accepted it.

205
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,133
That's why I'm trying
to avoid you, Red.

206
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,767
Yen! Yen!

207
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:52,733
Have you ever thought that
trying to avoid me is like

208
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:55,700
proving to me that your mom
is guilty?

209
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,833
Red, I'm staying away from you

210
00:12:56,900 --> 00:13:01,633
because I don't want to cause
my mom more pain.

211
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,767
Ever since your family
put her in jail,

212
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:07,133
I saw everything that
she'd been through.

213
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:10,100
Until now that she has gotten
out of jail,

214
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,967
your family is still making her
life miserable!

215
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:17,500
I don't want to cause her
any more pain

216
00:13:17,567 --> 00:13:20,367
once she finds out I have
a connection with you.

217
00:13:21,633 --> 00:13:25,633
The son of the woman who sent
her to jail.

218
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:29,233
But did you ever think about me?

219
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:34,933
Didn't you ever think
that I'm suffering too?

220
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:38,767
Yen, it's also hard for me.

221
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:45,867
Because the woman I love is
connected to my brother's death.

222
00:13:45,933 --> 00:13:47,967
That's painful. It hurts!

223
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,700
I was there when the crime
was committed, Red.

224
00:13:50,767 --> 00:13:52,933
I saw everything.

225
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:57,800
I saw how hard my mom tried
to save your brother.

226
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,800
That's why I know
she's innocent.

227
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:02,967
My mom is innocent!

228
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,500
What do you mean?

229
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:06,433
What are you trying to say?

230
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,100
Were you there? Did you see
everything that happened?

231
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:09,567
- Did you?
- Yes, Red!

232
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:11,133
I was there!

233
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:15,500
I saw when your former driver
forced his way in.

234
00:14:15,567 --> 00:14:17,167
My mom didn't want
to let him in.

235
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,033
I'm glad you're here.

236
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:23,867
I just need to get something
from the quarters.

237
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,200
I just need to get my stuff.

238
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:27,233
I thought you already got
all your stuff.

239
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,700
Why do you have to come back
here?

240
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,800
And you can't come in here.
Because my employer's not here.

241
00:14:30,867 --> 00:14:32,067
You're acting as if
I'm a stranger.

242
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:33,200
I can't let you in.

243
00:14:33,267 --> 00:14:34,500
I worked here longer than you.

244
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,933
But you don't work here anymore.

245
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,700
Don't you trust me?

246
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,167
You're not allowed
to come in here.

247
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:42,533
Who is this girl?

248
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,167
My daughter.

249
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:47,067
Did your grumpy employer
let you bring her here?

250
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:49,933
Fine, I'll take you
to the quarters.

251
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,033
Just get all your stuff together
and leave right away.

252
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,133
Okay.

253
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,367
Make it quick. Get your stuff
and go.

254
00:14:56,433 --> 00:14:58,533
I'm busy.

255
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,833
And then I saw your driver
stealing something.

256
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:07,867
That's why I told my mom.

257
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:09,100
Why are you taking that?

258
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,300
Be quiet. I'll hit you!

259
00:15:10,367 --> 00:15:12,100
- Mom! He's taking something!
- I said be quiet!

260
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:14,033
- What are you taking?
- Stay out of this!

261
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,167
Mom!

262
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:19,967
And then he panicked.

263
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:22,300
We followed him into the garage.

264
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:24,567
This is what we're going to use
when we meet up.

265
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:26,233
Okay, bye!

266
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,833
Raul! No!

267
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,767
But we were too late.

268
00:15:37,533 --> 00:15:42,433
He ran your brother over
without mercy.

269
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:46,867
That's not what my mom told me.

270
00:15:46,933 --> 00:15:49,367
I'm not asking you
to believe me.

271
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,233
But that's what I saw.

272
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:59,900
I can't blame you for believing
in your family.

273
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:01,200
They're your family.

274
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:08,033
But Red, we can't meet halfway.

275
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,500
So we should just break up.

276
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:21,333
I know it's hard, but we don't
have a choice.

277
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:27,433
So let's just do it...

278
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,633
for my mom's peace of mind
and your family's sake.

279
00:17:42,467 --> 00:17:44,267
Hi, Friend!

280
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:45,533
Are you okay?

281
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:50,300
Red found out the truth already.

282
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:55,267
He already knows my mom's
connection to his family.

283
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,367
I thought I could handle it.

284
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:04,000
But it hurts to face the truth.

285
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:08,667
Eden...

286
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:12,767
It's better that he found out
sooner.

287
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:19,333
So you both wouldn't have
to waste all your time

288
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:22,967
loving each other. Right?

289
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:26,133
I know I have to do this.

290
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,967
It's for the better...

291
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:31,433
for my mom's sake.

292
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:36,200
It just hurts to get mad
at the person

293
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:38,800
who taught me how to love.

294
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,733
Bro, that's enough.

295
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:02,167
You're drunk.

296
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:05,933
It felt funny and irritating
at the same time.

297
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:12,400
Who would have thought
that my teammate, Peter,

298
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:16,933
would backstab me?

299
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:20,300
You know what I mean? I felt
like I was blindsided

300
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:23,067
by the person I trusted so much.

301
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,533
And that's not cool, bro!

302
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,833
We cheers to that!

303
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:30,767
Cheers!

304
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:34,833
Bro, are you okay?

305
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:40,133
I'm okay.

306
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,133
I just want to talk about...

307
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,467
Hey.

308
00:19:46,533 --> 00:19:50,433
Why are we talking about
that Peter incident again?

309
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:53,100
Bro, that was before
the plane crash.

310
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,567
That was a long time ago!

311
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,667
Is that so?

312
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:03,467
I can't distinguish
what happened before

313
00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:05,567
and what's happening now.

314
00:20:08,367 --> 00:20:18,333
Because it feels the same
when you get betrayed

315
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:21,000
by someone you love.

316
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:29,100
Help! Help!

317
00:20:29,167 --> 00:20:30,700
Miss, hold on to me!

318
00:20:30,767 --> 00:20:32,000
Come on!

319
00:20:37,567 --> 00:20:38,900
Thank you, thank you.

320
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:41,933
I thought I was
the only survivor.

321
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,367
Are you okay?

322
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,600
Yeah, I'm good.

323
00:20:45,667 --> 00:20:47,000
You look familiar.

324
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:49,733
You're that guy at the campus.

325
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,300
By the way, I'm Red.

326
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:58,467
Look! It won't turn on anymore!

327
00:20:58,533 --> 00:20:59,800
It's all your fault.

328
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:01,367
- Why are you blaming me?
- You wasted it!

329
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:09,633
If we can find a reason
to laugh, why deprive ourselves?

330
00:21:09,733 --> 00:21:12,600
Sorry, but your jokes
are not helping.

331
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:15,967
What are you doing? I don't know
how you can take this lightly!

332
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:18,233
I'm not taking our situation
lightly.

333
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:19,600
I just want it to be bearable.

334
00:21:19,667 --> 00:21:22,367
I was just trying to...

335
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:23,767
Never mind.

336
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:27,700
Are you feeling sick?

337
00:21:27,767 --> 00:21:28,633
No.

338
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:30,367
I think you have a fever.

339
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:31,700
No. It's nothing.

340
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:36,433
I just got rained on yesterday
after getting all sweaty.

341
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,967
Probably that's why I wasn't
feeling so good.

342
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:40,767
I just need some rest.
I'll be fine.

343
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,567
Okay, eat this first.

344
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:46,567
And then we'll go back to our
shelter to get some rest.

345
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:49,767
We'll fight together, okay?

346
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:52,000
Red, you'll get better.

347
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:13,667
There! There's smoke already!

348
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:32,200
You're the best thing that
happened to me on this island.

349
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,400
Having found you...

350
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:36,567
knowing you.

351
00:22:36,633 --> 00:22:38,833
Your boyfriend must be lucky.

352
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:39,833
What boyfriend?

353
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,567
I don't have a boyfriend.

354
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:43,633
What happened? Did you break up?

355
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:45,233
How can we break up?

356
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,400
I never had a boyfriend.

357
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,367
As in never?

358
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:51,267
Since birth.

359
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:55,100
Then you can get a boyfriend
here.

360
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:56,167
How can I do that?

361
00:22:56,233 --> 00:22:58,133
You're the only guy here.

362
00:22:58,200 --> 00:23:00,233
Lucky you.

363
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,833
Crazy.

364
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:04,600
Who wouldn't go crazy about you?

365
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,600
Maybe there's a small chance,

366
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:12,933
but I'll hold on to that chance
no matter how small it is.

367
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,700
I'll keep fighting.

368
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:18,267
Yen, hopelessness
is our enemy here.

369
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:20,433
We can't let it beat us.

370
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:23,400
Don't be unfair!

371
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:26,267
Your family's been unfair
to my mom too.

372
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:27,267
What do you mean?

373
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:29,000
Stop following me, Red.

374
00:23:29,067 --> 00:23:31,267
- Just leave me alone.
- Yen!

375
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:32,500
What are you talking about?

376
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:35,167
That my family's been unfair
to your mom?

377
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:16,700
Are you sure that Amanda
had something to do

378
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:19,000
with my brother's death?

379
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:20,533
Why are you asking that?

380
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:21,633
What are you trying to say?

381
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:23,200
That we're just making up
stories?

382
00:24:23,267 --> 00:24:25,833
I just want to know what really
happened.

383
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,767
I deserve to know the truth,
right?

384
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:29,733
So what are you saying?
That you believe that woman

385
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:31,133
over me and your dad?

386
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:33,233
Ever since he met you,

387
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:35,567
our relationship wasn't the only
thing that got ruined.

388
00:24:35,633 --> 00:24:37,767
You're ruining his life too!

389
00:24:37,833 --> 00:24:41,933
If you're doing this to get Red
back, he's all yours.

390
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,167
If you like, I can give you
a leash to keep him with you.

391
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:46,533
I'll admit.

392
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:53,867
My investigation came to a point
where Amanda could be innocent.
